SIMPLE: punic
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Punic
<hw>Pu"nic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>Punicus</ets>
pertaining to Carthage, or its inhabitants, fr. <ets>Poeni</ets> the
Carthaginians.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to the ancient
Carthaginians.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Characteristic of the ancient Carthaginians;
faithless; treacherous; <as>as, <ex>Punic</ex> faith</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Yes, yes, his faith attesting nations own;⟦br⟧
'T is <qex>Punic</qex> all, and to a proverb known.</q> <rj><qau> H.
Brooke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Punice</ent>⟦br⟧
